# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Overlapp environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values. `.env.local` is
# gitignored — never commit real keys. Restart `next dev` after editing.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── REQUIRED for Phase 1 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase project URL. Dashboard → Project Settings → API → "Project URL".
# Looks like: https://abcdefghijklmno.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=

# Supabase anon / publishable key (safe for the browser; RLS is the real guard).
# Dashboard → Project Settings → API → "Project API keys" → anon / public.
# (If your project shows the newer "publishable" key — sb_publishable_... —
#  use that here instead; supabase-js accepts either.)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Public base URL of the app — used for auth email redirects and invite links.
# Local dev: http://localhost:3000  ·  Prod: your deployed origin.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ── SERVER-ONLY secret (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix → never sent to the browser) ──

# Service-role key. Bypasses RLS — used only by server-side code (e.g. the
# Phase 2 calendar-sync worker, admin tasks). Not strictly needed to start P1,
# but scaffold it now. Dashboard → API → service_role (or sb_secret_... ).
# ⚠️ Treat like a root password. Never expose to the client or commit it.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEFERRED — leave blank until the relevant phase. Listed so the shape is known.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Phase 2: Google Calendar sync (Google → Microsoft → Apple) ──
# Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 client (Web).
# Full walkthrough: docs/GOOGLE-SETUP.md. The OAuth client's authorized redirect
# URI must be exactly  ${NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL}/api/calendars/google/callback
# (e.g. http://localhost:3000/api/calendars/google/callback for local dev).
# Leave these blank and the Calendars page shows a "not configured" notice
# instead of the Connect button — the rest of the app is unaffected.
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Background re-sync (app/api/cron/sync-calendars). Any scheduler that sends
# `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` triggers a sync of all stale calendars.
# Generate one with `openssl rand -hex 32`. Without it the cron route 500s.
# CRON_SECRET=

# ── Phase 2 (later): Microsoft Graph / Outlook ──
# MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=
# MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Phase 4: Web Push (VAPID keys; generate with `npx web-push generate-vapid-keys`) ──
# NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
# VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT an app env var — configured in the Supabase dashboard, not here:
#   • Resend (auth email) → Dashboard → Authentication → SMTP Settings.
#     Built-in Supabase email is fine for local dev; wire Resend before prod.
#   • Google OAuth *login* provider → Dashboard → Authentication → Providers
#     (separate from the Phase 2 calendar OAuth above).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
